Aversion to Daylight	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:NightshadeSubRaceTrait.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Nightshades are creatures of utter darkness and loathe all light. If exposed to natural daylight (not merely a daylight spell), they take a -4 penalty on all attack rolls, saving throws, and skill checks.	KEY:Nightshade ~ Aversion to Daylight																											SOURCEPAGE:MM1	
Desecrating Aura	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:NightshadeSubRaceTrait.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:All nightshades give off a 20-foot radius emanation of utter desecration, imbuing their surroundings with negative energy. This ability works much like a desecrate spell, except that the nightshade's evil is so great that it is treated as the shrine of an evil power. All undead within 20 feet of the nightshade (including the creature itself ) gain a +2 profane bonus on attack rolls, damage rolls, and saving throws, and +2 hit points per HD. (The nightshade Hit Dice, attack, and save entries given here include these profane bonuses.) Charisma checks made to turn undead within this area take a -6 penalty. A nightshade's desecrating aura cannot be dispelled except by a dispel evil spell or similar effect. If the effect is dispelled, the nightshade can resume it as a free action on its next turn. Its desecrating aura is suppressed if a nightshade enters a consecrated or hallowed area, but the nightshade's presence also suppresses the consecrated or hallowed effect for as long as it remains in the area.	KEY:Nightshade ~ Desecrating Aura				DEFINE:DesecratingBonus|0					BONUS:VAR|DesecratingBonus|2	BONUS:COMBAT|TOHIT.Weapon|DesecratingBonus|TYPE=Profane	BONUS:COMBAT|TOHIT.GRAPPLE|DesecratingBonus|TYPE=Profane	BONUS:COMBAT|DAMAGE.Weapon|DesecratingBonus|TYPE=Profane						BONUS:SAVE|ALL|DesecratingBonus|TYPE=Profane	BONUS:HP|CURRENTMAX|DesecratingBonus*HD								SOURCEPAGE:MM1	
																																	
